ul core coverage: its resolved runtime dependencies are Kotlin stdlib/reflect and kotlinx-coroutines, and the artifact includes default decoders plus a built-in Java properties parser. Core behavior can be exercised with MapPropertySource, system/environment property sources, or .props/.properties inputs without Docker, extra Maven modules, or required environment setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"README examples often use YAML/JSON/TOML/HOCON configuration files; those formats require separate hoplite-yaml, hoplite-json, hoplite-toml, or hoplite-hocon modules. For a hoplite-core-only workflow, tests should prefer MapPropertySource or .props/.properties resources unless intentionally covering an integration module.\",\n    \"Default property sources can observe the host environment, system properties, user home config, or XDG config. Tests should keep assertions deterministic by using explicit property sources when practical.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_011b7b82b252ed84016a3f18cca18c8190a4d5e7c17b208812\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 7008, "output": 1268, "cacheRead": 39936, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 48212, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782519995008, "responseId": "resp_011b7b82b252ed84016a3f18bb8d908190be62a0a66cbf5f00"}, "toolResults": []}
